WITH 2022 gradually unfolding, Laolu Gbenjo and his LG Band are in full preparations for his upcoming US tour of different cities. The tour, The Nation gathered, is anticipated to be an extensive musical tour where Laolu Gbenjo will promote the rich Nigerian cultural heritage, norms, and values to esteemed fans and lovers of good music.   Why the future of rap in Nigeria is exciting – AO-Machine     I don’t want to be a social media husband, says Stan Nze     I don’t see anything wrong with two adults recording…   Speaking about the forthcoming event, the entertainer said, “I do highlife, contemporary highlife, juju music which is deeply rooted in African and Nigerian Music. Attendees of the tour should expect an electrifying performance seasoned with a lot of energy, dance, and an atmosphere of happiness all around.” Laolu started singing in 2008 and has performed across different states in Nigeria, Ghana, Benin, the UK, and virtual shows across the globe. While the U.S. tour has been put together by Sammek Moments Arts and Cultural Entertainment, Laolu is set for another performance in April 2022 in the U.K. SPONSORED